definitions.definition: A piece of knowledge that is hidden and intended to be kept hidden.
examples: "Can you keep a secret ?" "Yes." "So can I."

definitions.definition: The key or principle by which something is made clear; the knack .
examples: The secret to a long-lasting marriage is compromise.
The work was done in secret , so that nobody could object.

definitions.definition: Any prayer spoken inaudibly and not aloud; especially, one of the prayers in the Tridentine Mass , immediately following the "orate, fratres", said inaudibly by the celebrant .

main_definition: ( countable ) A piece of knowledge that is hidden and intended to be kept hidden. [from late 14th c.]
secondary_definitions: The key or principle by which something is made clear; the knack .
( archaic , in the plural ) The genital organs .
( historical ) A form of steel skullcap .

( Christianity , often in the plural ) Any prayer spoken inaudibly and not aloud; especially, one of the prayers in the Tridentine Mass , immediately following the "orate, fratres", said inaudibly by the celebrant .
